						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Petruza wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So if RTI is used to return from a BRK call, then the immediately following byte after the BRK instruction would be ignored.</div>
<br />Yes, which is why the Apple IIGS monitor disassembles BRK as if it took an 8-bit argument: "BRK $00" through "BRK $FF". You might think that would be useful for a syscall mechanism, but <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=816" class="postlink">the performance isn't there</a>.</div>

